Possession of a person is affected by the defect of precariousness if the person 
does not have a right of ownership in relation to the object he holds. According to French terminology, precarious possessions refer to the possession of those who hold a thing for another on basis of an agreement or in such quality that, at the expiratio
n of the agreement, or where they lose their quality, they must return the thing. Hence, the possession of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\i0\insrsid15484085\charrsid12875540 usufructory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b0\i0\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 , a limited user /usage/, a tenant farmer, leaseholder or a pledgee, a creditor secured by antichresis, a tutor with regard to a minor's property is affected by the defect of precariousness.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b0\i0\insrsid15484085\charrsid12875540 
