 interests with regard to which a possessory action can be brought are corporal immovable, their usufruct, servitudes and immovable rights of enjoyment and use. However, since possession of corporeal movable things /chattels/ is equivalent to ownership, t
he action applicable to them is negatory actions, i.e., actions based on title or ownership and that are intended to recover the same. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid14249632\charrsid12875540 
