Corporeal immovable things can be the object of 
possessory action bearing on possession of the land itself, only if they are in-commerce /private domain/ and are susceptible of being acquired by adverse possession/ acquisitive prescription. Hence, it shall not apply to things that are considered as par
t of the public domain. See Art 1444-1447 of the Civil Code.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid12588778\charrsid12875540 
