Furthermore, where one private person brings against another private person a possessory action and where only private interests are contested between them, the defendant cannot plead the charac
ter of public domain possessed, according to him, by the immovable in issue. The possessor of land expropriated for public purposes such as construction of local roads can bring a possessory action against the municipality, which would contest his right t
o be compensated. This action does not aim at retention or recovery of possession, but at the recognition for the purpose of establishing his title to the compensation.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid12588778\charrsid12875540 
