\ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 Right of ownership is the widest and the ultimate property right that may be had in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid14302104\charrsid12875540 relation to things or objects. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 Ownership may be defined as legal relationship that gives rise to certain rights and obligations between persons in relation to an object. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid16266356\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
Ownership is said to be absolute in the sense that the owner may do as he likes with the thing that is his own. The rights of an owner include; 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1.\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar
\jclisttab\tx360\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls8\ilvl1\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0\pararsid11346195 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
The right of use and enjoyment, which includes the right to determine to what type of use the object may be put, to deal with the fruits of the thing as he likes, and even the right to destroy the thing or its fruits.  Arts 1205/1/ and 1270-1271 of
 the Civil Code.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2.\tab}
The right of possession that includes the right to exclude others. Property right is essentially a guarantee of the exclusion of other persons from the use and handling of the thing over which the right is exercised and the right to rec
laim it from the hands of another.  Arts 1204, 1148 and 1149 of the Civil Code.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3.\tab}
 The right to transfer the thing and its fruits for consideration or gratuitously which could be intervivos / while the owner is alive / or mortis causa/ up on his death/ an
d the right to charge them as security (mortgage or pledge). Arts 1205/2/ and 3049/2/ of the Civil Code.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 4.\tab}The right to leave or abandon the thing or its fruits at will.  Art 1189 of the Civil Code.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}\pard \ltrpar
