Ownership is said to be 'exclusive' because these rights are in principle available only to the owner, and is "perpetual" since these rights are neither extinguished by non-usage nor limited by duration. See Art 1204 of the Civil Code. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid16266356\charrsid12875540 
