The fact that an owner may cede so many rights and still retain ownership raises difficulties of definition. From this we can consider ownership as the magnetic core which remains when all present rights of enjoyment are removed from it and 
which attracts to itself the various elements temporarily held by others as they lapse.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid16266356\charrsid12875540 
