\af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 right to dispose of his share of rights in the undivided interest in the thing jointly owned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 . See Art
 1260 of the Civil Code. Hence, a joint owner may sale, donate, pledge or mortgage his share of right in the thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2171397\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 5.\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 Each joint owner has the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 right to request termination of joint ownership}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 . In other words, each co-owner has the right to request the cou
rt, at any time, for partition or division of the thing or the sale by auction of the thing and division of the proceeds of the sale. If the thing jointly owned is a movable thing, a joint owner may apply for sale by an auction. See 1271. This right canno
t be waived by agreement.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}\pard \ltrpar
