1
 of the Civil Code. Where the beneficiaries have the same degree of relationship, they shall exercise the right of recovery together and shall become joint owners of the immovable recovered. See Art 1393 of the Civil Code. However, among persons who are i
n
 the same degree of relationship, those who live on the land or participate by their personal work in its exploitation are given priority over others. See Art 1392 of the Civil Code. Furthermore, Art 1396 excludes right of recovery of relatives where the 
i
mmovable transferred is situated in urban area/ town planning area/ or where it mainly consists of a dwelling house or some other building.  These provisions also imply that the right of recovery relatives under is limited to cases where rural farmland co
mmunally held by a family/ rest land/ is transferred.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid1342864\charrsid12875540  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
