hat public purpose exists only where the undertaking for which the property is to be expropriated is to be directly used or enjoyed by the public, Such as schools, hospital, roads etc. Unlike the first view, this view proposes a strict interpretation of t
h
e concept and requires the public to be the direct beneficiary of the proposed undertaking and to which it shall have equal and direct access. In other words, expropriation for a purpose, which may indirectly benefit the public is not justifiable or is un
lawful.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid3038988\charrsid12875540  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
Hence this view tends to limit the power of the government in expropriation private property.           }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid12266100\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
When we examine the rules of the civil code in this regard, we find that the civil code does not provide the concept of public purpose. Howeve
r, it clearly provides that the state may not expropriate private property solely for the purpose of generating income or financial benefits. Hence, generating revenue for the government does not constitute \lquote public purpose\rquote 
 and taking private property on t
his ground would be unjustifiable and unlawful. See Art 1464/1/ of the code. However, where the project for which the land is required would also benefit the local community/ the public/ by increasing the value of properties in the area the project shall 
b
e deemed to serve public purpose and expropriation is possible. See Art 1464/2/ of the code. It is also possible to argue that a proposed project would serve public purpose where it benefits the local community by creating job opportunities, creating mark
et for raw materials\'85etc.  In other words, indirect public benefit from the proposed project constitutes public purpose under the civil code.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid12266100\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
According to Article 1463 of the Civil Code, the competent authorities must determine whether the project for w
hich the land is required serves public purpose or not and a notice to this effect has to be published. In certain circumstances, public inquiry may be necessary before such declaration is made and published, i.e., the declaration will only be made after 
the public is consulted and interested person have expressed their views regarding the project. See Art 1465 of the code. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid227751\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
According to Art 2/5/ of the Expropriation of Landholdings for Public Purposes and Payment of Compensation Pro No 455/2005 a propose
d project shall be deemed to serve public purpose where the appropriate body decides, pursuant to the urban structure or development plan;}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid227751\charrsid12875540  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 That it ensures the right of the public to benefit directly or indirectly from the use of the, land}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid227751\charrsid12875540  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 That it helps to achieve and consolidate sustainable socio-economic development.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid227751\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
Similarly, according to Art 2/7/ of the Re-enactment of Urban Land Lease Holding Pro No 272/2002, \lquote public interest\rquote  means that which an appropriate body determines as a public interest i
n conformity with the master plan or development plan in order to continuously ensure the direct or indirect usability of land by peoples, and to progressively enhance urban development. 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s4\qj \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel3\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11346195 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\i\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc229915110}EXPROPRIATION PROCEDURES UNDER THE CIVIL CODE{\*\bkmkend _Toc229915110}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx1860\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11346195 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 
