\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar
\qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls127\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0\pararsid11346195 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 Art 3 (1) of the proclamation provides that only a woreda administration, where the land to be expropriated is situated in rural
 areas, and a city administration, where the land to be expropriated is situated in urban areas, shall have the power to expropriate land.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid357957\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
 Generally, a land holding may be expropriated only where the project for the implementation of which the land is r
equired serves public purpose. According to Art 2/5/ a proposed project is said to serve a public purpose where it is in accordance with urban structure plan or development plan, brings about a sustainable socio-economic development and, directly or indir
ectly, benefits the public. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid13909151\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
Expropriation order may be made where a woreda or city administration or higher federal or regional government organs, decides that the land holding in question should be used for \lquote  a better development project\rquote  to be carried 
out by the government, public enterprises, private investors, co-operatives or other organs. Furthermore, expropriation order may be used to terminate a lease contract where the holder fails to comply with the obligations he under took in the contract of 
lease and the relevant laws. See Art 3/1/ and /2/.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid13909151\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
The woreda or city administration, which decided to expropriate a land holding according to Arts 2/5/ and 3, shall notify, in writing, the landholder of the expropriation order. The notice must indicate t
he time when the holder must vacate the land and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid13909151\charrsid12875540 amount}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
 of compensation to be paid to him. The period within which the holder must vacate the land may not be less than 90 days. The landholder who has been given notice of the expropriation shall vacate his land }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid13909151\charrsid12875540 within}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
 90 days of the date of payment of compensation or from the date of deposit of the compensation a blocked account to be opened in the name of the organ issuing the order where the holder refuses to accept the compensation. However, where the
re are no crops, trees or other properties in the land to be expropriated, the holder must hand over the land }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid13909151\charrsid12875540 within}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540  30 days of receipt of the expropriation order. The expropriating body may use police force to vacate and take possession of the land. See Art 4.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid11346195\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 
The implementing agency, w/c may be a federal or state organ or public enterprise, private investor, cooperative or any other organ intending to implement the project must prepare data relating to the land required for its use, its e
xact location and send to the woreda or city administration at least one year before commencement of the project and obtain the permission to use the land. It shall also pay compensation to the person whose landholding is expropriated. See Art 5. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid11346195\charrsid12875540 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f10\fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 \loch\af10\dbch\af0\hich\f10 \'fc\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540 Where 
utility lines, such as water, sewerage, telephone, electric or gas lines cross over or under the land required for the project, the implementing agency shall request, in writing, the owner of the lines to remove them. The request must indicate the exact l
ocation of the lines. The owner of the lines who received the request must determine the cost of removal and reinstallation of the lines and send details of its evaluation to the implementing agency }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs28\insrsid11346195\charrsid12875540 within}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540  a period of 30 days. The agency shall pay the compe
nsation with in a period of 30 days from the date of receipt of valuation. The owner of the lines shall remove the lines and vacate the land }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid11346195\charrsid12875540 within}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid2119398\charrsid12875540  60 days of receipt of compensation. See Art 6.
