Prior to the emergence of use of documents in contracts, people tried various techniques intended to ensure security of p
roperty rights. For instance, the seller of land used to transfer ownership and guarantee the buyer by handing over a handful of earth from the land to the latter in the presence of neighbors. Similarly, Owners of land used to declare their right to it us
ing various signs, such as enclosures and inscriptions on trees. With the emergence and prevalence of documents, people tried to ensure security by developing customs, which require the deposit of acts creating or transferring rights on immovable things. 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs28\insrsid13909151\charrsid12875540 
