 systems register ownership or other right, such as usufruct, servitude or mortgage rather than the acts or contracts creating such rights. Registration under this system is 
a conclusive proof of the right unless the person registered as owner acted fraudulently. In other words, a person who, in good faith, acquired an immovable from a person who is registered as an owner and have his right registered will acquire a genuine r
ight of ownership even where the transferor was not a true owner or the transferor acquired the immovable under an invalid contract. 
