nables a potential buyer or mortgagee to ascertain that he or she is dealing with a person who is entitled to sell or mortgage the thing, i.e., the owner and acquire 
a legally enforceable right of ownership or mortgage. In the absence of a system of registration a person who intends to buy or secure his rights with mortgage will not be able know whether the person he is dealing with an actual owner and runs the risk o
f dispossession or eviction or inability to enforce his mortgage. See Arts 2884 and 3049 of the Civil Code.
